### Core Difference

| Feature                  | **Flexbox**                                      | **CSS Grid**                                          |
|--------------------------|--------------------------------------------------|-------------------------------------------------------|
| **Dimension**            | **1D** (sirf ek direction – row ya column)       | **2D** (rows + columns dono ek saath)                 |
| **Focus**                | Content flow (items content ke hisab se adjust hote hain) | Precise placement (layout pehle define, items usme fit hote hain) |
| **Wrapping**             | `flex-wrap` se multiple lines, content-driven     | Auto-placement + responsive without many media queries |
| **Gap**                  | Native nahi (negative margin hack lagta tha)     | Native `gap` / `grid-gap` (bahut clean)               |
| **Alignment**            | Items ke beech spacing aur alignment mein strong | Dono axes (horizontal + vertical) mein perfect control |
| **Spanning Items**       | Mushkil                                          | Bahut asaan (`grid-column: span 2;`)                  |

### Kab Kya Use Karein? (Decision Guide)

**Flexbox Use Karo Jab:**
- Content-driven layout chahiye (items ka size content ke hisab se badle)
- Simple alignment (center, space-between, stretch)
- Navigation menus, button groups, card ke andar content
- Items ko wrap karna ho aur flexible space distribution chahiye
- Sticky footer, equal height in one direction

**CSS Grid Use Karo Jab:**
- Precise 2D structure chahiye (overall page layout)
- Card grids, image galleries, dashboards
- Items ko multiple rows/columns mein span karna ho
- Responsive layouts with fewer media queries (`auto-fit` + `minmax()`)
- Asymmetrical ya complex overlapping designs

**Hybrid Approach (Sabse Recommended):**
- **Badi structure** (page layout) → **Grid**
- **Chhote components** (card ke andar, nav items) → **Flexbox**

**Example:**
```css
/* Outer layout - Grid */
.page {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 250px 1fr;
  gap: 2rem;
}

/* Inner component - Flexbox */
.card {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  justify-content: space-between;
}
```

### Pros & Cons

**Flexbox**
- **Pros**: Content ke hisab se flexible, alignment bohot easy, purane browsers mein better support
- **Cons**: 2D control limited, gap ke liye hack, kabhi unexpected behavior

**CSS Grid**
- **Pros**: True 2D control, native gap, powerful responsive (auto-fit), clean code
- **Cons**: Purane browsers (IE) mein support weak tha (ab 2026 mein almost perfect)
